com.pb.aquavis.emfac2011

Class Emfac2011Properties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.property.PropertyDeluxe
      • com.pb.aquavis.emfac2011.Emfac2011Properties

  • public class Emfac2011Properties
extends PropertyDeluxe
    The Emfac2011Properties holds the properties used by the various classes in this package. The property keys listed in this class (as public static final constants) must all be present in the instantiated properties object, or it will throw an error during construction. Additionally, the AREAS_PROPERTY must be typed correctly as a map from a string to a list holding strings (see its documentation for more information).

      • AREAS_PROPERTY

        public static final java.lang.String AREAS_PROPERTY
        The property key for the mapping from EMFAC2011 areas to model districts used for the model run. These areas must be specified as a parsable map from a string key to a string list. That is, the property entry should look something like the following: 
        
     emfac.2011.area(MSLS) = {El Dorado (LT):[El],Placer (LT):[Pl]}
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • MODEL_VMT_INCLUDES_NON_MUTABLES_PROPERTY

        public static final java.lang.String MODEL_VMT_INCLUDES_NON_MUTABLES_PROPERTY
        The property key for the boolean indicating whether or not the model (travel demand, not EMFAC) VMT includes totals for non-mutable vehicle types. If it does, then the VMT will be scaled before adjusting the EMFAC input file.
        See Also:

      • XLS_CONVERTER_PROGRAM_PROPERTY

        public static final java.lang.String XLS_CONVERTER_PROGRAM_PROPERTY
        The property key for the location of the xls converter program. This program converts the malformed EMFAC2011 reference files to a (strictly) valid format, which can then be used by the rest of the model.
